  <prompt>
The R7 W11 POC implemented `EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs` to populate per-bullet `primaryEntityType`/`primaryEntityId`/`primaryEntityName` for click-through. With T131 expanding to 6 entity types (events / documents / matters / projects / todos), verify the enrichment logic correctly resolves entity refs for ALL 6 types — not just events. Fix any gaps.
  </prompt>

  <role>
You are a BFF service developer verifying cross-cutting projection logic across new entity types. Targeted code modification if gaps found; investigation otherwise.
  </role>

  <goal>
Every bullet rendered in Daily Briefing widget has a working entity link (primaryEntityType / primaryEntityId / primaryEntityName populated) regardless of which of the 6 channels it came from. UAT-verifiable: operator clicks ANY bullet → navigates to correct entity record.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    - Current `EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs` implementation in `DailyBriefingNarrator` (R7 W11)
    - Entity types to verify: sprk_event (existing), sprk_document, sprk_matter, sprk_project, sprk_todo (new from T131)
    - BriefingItem projection contains entity metadata per T131
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
