  <notes>
    **Status**: COMPLETED 2026-06-30 (R7 W12.2 task 135)

    **Verification outcome** — `EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs` is implemented as a generic matcher (not per-entity branches). It works for all 6 entity types in the dominant case (item has a populated RegardingId — either parent matter/project for Tasks/Documents/ToDos, or self for Matter/Project rows).

    **Gap found + fixed**: orphan items (no regarding matter — common for sprk_event tasks without sprk_regardingmatter, and sprk_todo without regarding) produced bullets with empty PrimaryEntityType/Id, causing the widget's click-through link to be hidden (NarrativeBullet.tsx line 390 condition fails). Per task goal "every bullet has a working entity link", this is a real UX defect.

    **Fix**: Three-tier resolution in EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs:
      - **Tier 1** (dominant): first match with populated `RegardingId` → click goes to matter/project (preserves existing behavior).
      - **Tier 2** (NEW, orphan fallback): first match with populated `SourceEntityType` + `Id` → click goes to the source entity row (e.g., orphan Task → sprk_event row).
      - **Tier 3** (defensive): first match overall → name-only (widget hides link).

    **Files modified**:
      - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/DailyBriefingEndpoints.cs` — added `SourceEntityType` field to `ChannelItemDto` record.
      - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Narrators/DailyBriefingCollector.cs` — populate `SourceEntityType = i.EntityType` in `ToChannel` projection.
      - `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Narrators/DailyBriefingNarrator.cs` — three-tier `EnrichBulletWithEntityRefs` resolution.
      - `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Narrators/DailyBriefingNarratorEntityLinkTests.cs` — NEW; 9 tests (7 theory cases per entity type + 2 facts for unmatched / tier-preference).

    **Verification**:
      - 9 new tests pass; 34/34 DailyBriefing-area tests pass.
      - Release publish: 48.5 MB compressed (NFR-01 ceiling 60 MB).
      - No new packages / DI registrations / endpoints / abstractions.
      - CLAUDE.md §11 component justification satisfied (one field extension to existing DTO with named concrete failure mode).
  </notes>
</task>
